HEADWORD: Egoist
<hw>E"go*ist</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧go⟦ium⟧ste</ets>.
See <er>Egoism</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One given overmuch to
egoism or thoughts of self.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I, dullard <qex>egoist</qex>, taking no special recognition of
such nobleness.</q> <rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Philos.)</fld> <def>A believer in egoism.</def></p>

<p><ent>Egoistical</ent>⟦br⟧
